 ('119', 'field', '25', 'en_us', ' together with our brand strategy partners at stoke turnstyle is breaking ground on a new 5 000 sq foot office in august 2016 the building will serve as home for 20 strategists designers and developers located on canal street the park side project borders the burke gilman trail and overlooks the fremont cut waterway the firms continue to grow and our need for space was at odds with the long term lease trends of seattle said stoke partner erin quick it makes good financial sense for the businesses and for the firms practices we re creating a unique place where creative thinkers can do their best work and clients can collaborate with us in new and different ways on the street level a cafe style collaboration space serves as a foundation to two levels with open floor studios and meeting space designed with 16 floor to ceiling windows the plan takes advantage of the views over the trail and canal the work areas will be bathed with natural light an open atrium at the center creates visual interest with the benefit of passive solar design said ben graham partner at turnstyle it s a design friendly environment that makes the best of our open collaborative work style the commercial office market is racing and the long term value for buyers in seattle looks good noted graham as the business environment accelerates having a place that minimizes our commutes offers easy access to downtown with everyday access to great restaurants and enhances mobility options on the burke gilman trail all with a deck and a view seemed like a winning combination the architecture was led by award winning heliotrope of ballard seattle s western ventures serves as the general contractor construction is targeted for completion in june 2017 '),
